Nelson Mandela from Makueni won the men's Under-20 8km race in 21:27.5, beating Japan-based student Philip Kilonzo to second place in 21:29.2 as James Mwanzia timed 21:34.4 for third place.Julius Muasya from Makueni claimed the boys' Under-18 contest in 16:36.3 after seeing off compatriot Caleb Munyalo in 17:20.6 as  Machakos' James Musembi clocked 17:11.6 for third. The 2018 Africa Youth Olympics 1,500m champion Nickson Lesiyia transitioned to senior ranks in style after blowing away the field to win the senior men's 10km race during the Athletics Kenya Southern Cross Country Championships on Saturday at Machakos People's Park.
The 20-year-old Lesiyia from Makueni stayed behind 2018 Youth Olympics 3,000m champion Jackson Kavesa from Machakos and Emmanuel Lemama of Makueni, who exchanged leads in the initial laps.



